@*
    Onboarding overlay — shown once per user (localStorage) on first authenticated page load.
    Users can dismiss with the close button or tick "Don't show again".
*@
<div id="kronOnboard" class="kron-onboard-backdrop" style="display:none;" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="kron-onboard-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="kronOnboardTitle">
        <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-close" id="kronOnboardClose" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
        <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-arrow left" id="kronOnboardPrev" aria-label="Previous">&#10094;</button>
        <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-arrow right" id="kronOnboardNext" aria-label="Next">&#10095;</button>

        <div class="kron-onboard-slide active" data-step="1">
            <div class="kron-onboard-illustration">📜</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-title" id="kronOnboardTitle">Capture the spark</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-tagline">A memory finds you. Catch it before it disappears.</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-body">
                A song, a smell, a face on the train — your past arrives unannounced.
                Open Kronoscript, type three lines, tap <strong>Post</strong>. Thirty seconds,
                done. Tomorrow you'll have something you would have lost.
            </div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-example">
                <em>Cleopatra walks the harbor at sunset, 30 BC. The salt brings back a dinner thirty years earlier.</em><br />
                She opens Quick Story: "Salt and oil lamps tonight. Brought back the night that strange Roman wouldn't stop talking about libraries. I never told him I was scared of him."<br />
                <em>Posted. The walk continues.</em>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-slide" data-step="2">
            <div class="kron-onboard-illustration">📅</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-title">Pin it to your life</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-tagline">Yesterday or fifty years ago — every memory finds its place.</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-body">
                Just give it a year. Kronoscript files it on your timeline automatically.
                Skip across decades. Today you write about a phone call last week; tomorrow
                about your fifth birthday. Slowly, the chronology builds itself.
            </div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-example">
                <em>Cleopatra dates her harbor walk: today, 30 BC.</em><br />
                Then she dates the dinner she just remembered: 48 BC.<br />
                <em>Both land where they belong. She realizes she's been thinking about Caesar for thirty years without knowing it.</em>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-slide" data-step="3">
            <div class="kron-onboard-illustration">🤝</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-title">Let others add their side</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-tagline">Your memory, their memory, both true. Together they make a story.</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-body">
                Tag the people who lived an event with you. They get notified. They write the
                parts you forgot, the things they saw differently, the videos they had on their
                phone. Comments, reactions, photos — all attach to that single moment.
            </div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-example">
                <em>Cleopatra tags</em> <strong>@@JuliusCaesar</strong>. <em>From his timeline:</em>
                "I remember her hiding behind the wine pourer to see if I'd notice. I noticed."<br />
                <em>Decades later, their daughter Selene finds both versions and adds:</em>
                "Mother told me this story once. Father wrote it the same way. They were never as far apart as Rome believed."
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-slide" data-step="4">
            <div class="kron-onboard-illustration">🌳</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-title">Watch it grow over the years</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-tagline">One memory today. Three next month. A life in a decade.</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-body">
                Kronoscript reminds you: <em>"On this day, eight years ago, you wrote…"</em>
                Your timeline fills, your <strong>Working Index</strong> becomes a private memory map,
                and your story keeps writing itself even when you forget you're working on it.
            </div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-example">
                <em>Ten years later, Cleopatra opens Kronoscript on a quiet evening. On This Day shows her the harbor walk she wrote five years ago.</em>
                She reads it, smiles, and adds one line:
                "Five years on, I still walk the same route. The salt still hits the same way. He's still in it."<br />
                <em>That's not a journal entry. That's a layer.</em>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-slide" data-step="5">
            <div class="kron-onboard-illustration">📖</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-title">Take your story off the screen</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-tagline">When you're ready, hold your life in your hands.</div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-body">
                Reorder, edit, polish. Pull a chapter, add a foreword, drop in your favorite photos.
                Hit <strong>Export</strong> and walk away with a clean, dated, illustrated book.
                Yours forever — even if Kronoscript disappeared tomorrow.
            </div>
            <div class="kron-onboard-example">
                <em>Late in life, Cleopatra opens Export. She picks 50 BC to 30 BC and out comes a bound volume. She gives one copy to her son.</em><br />
                Centuries later, scholars find both books — hers and Caesar's — side by side.
                <em>The truth, told twice, by the only two people who could.</em>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-dots">
            <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-dot active" data-dot="1" aria-label="Step 1"></button>
            <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-dot" data-dot="2" aria-label="Step 2"></button>
            <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-dot" data-dot="3" aria-label="Step 3"></button>
            <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-dot" data-dot="4" aria-label="Step 4"></button>
            <button type="button" class="kron-onboard-dot" data-dot="5" aria-label="Step 5"></button>
        </div>

        <div class="kron-onboard-nav">
            <label class="dont-show">
                <input type="checkbox" id="kronOnboardDontShow" />
                Don't show this again
            </label>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-quick-story text-white px-3" id="kronOnboardDone" style="display:none;">Got it!</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
(function () {
    // v2: permanent dismissal key; session key so we only trigger once per
    // browser session (sign-in), not on every navigation.
    var PERMANENT_KEY = 'kronOnboardDismissed_v3';
    var SESSION_KEY   = 'kronOnboardSeenThisSession_v3';
    try { if (localStorage.getItem(PERMANENT_KEY) === '1') return; } catch (e) {}
    try { if (sessionStorage.getItem(SESSION_KEY) === '1') return; } catch (e) {}

    var backdrop = document.getElementById('kronOnboard');
    if (!backdrop) return;
    backdrop.style.display = 'flex';
    backdrop.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'false');
    try { sessionStorage.setItem(SESSION_KEY, '1'); } catch (e) {}

    var slides = backdrop.querySelectorAll('.kron-onboard-slide');
    var dots   = backdrop.querySelectorAll('.kron-onboard-dot');
    var prevBtn = document.getElementById('kronOnboardPrev');
    var nextBtn = document.getElementById('kronOnboardNext');
    var doneBtn = document.getElementById('kronOnboardDone');
    var closeBtn = document.getElementById('kronOnboardClose');
    var dontShow = document.getElementById('kronOnboardDontShow');
    var current = 0;

    function render() {
        slides.forEach(function (s, i) { s.classList.toggle('active', i === current); });
        dots.forEach(function (d, i) { d.classList.toggle('active', i === current); });
        prevBtn.style.visibility = (current === 0) ? 'hidden' : 'visible';
        var atEnd = current === slides.length - 1;
        nextBtn.style.visibility = atEnd ? 'hidden' : 'visible';
        doneBtn.style.display = atEnd ? 'inline-block' : 'none';
    }

    function dismiss() {
        if (dontShow && dontShow.checked) {
            try { localStorage.setItem(PERMANENT_KEY, '1'); } catch (e) {}
        }
        backdrop.style.display = 'none';
        backdrop.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
    }

    nextBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        if (current < slides.length - 1) { current++; render(); }
    });
    prevBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        if (current > 0) { current--; render(); }
    });
    doneBtn.addEventListener('click', dismiss);
    closeBtn.addEventListener('click', dismiss);
    dots.forEach(function (d, i) {
        d.addEventListener('click', function () { current = i; render(); });
    });
    backdrop.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
        if (e.target === backdrop) dismiss();
    });

    render();
})();
</script>
